# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
**Problems Looks Easy but how do you handle Overlaps conditions.**

here i used two priority queues one for **left side** and one for **right side** and i maintain a size equal to candidates.

to Handel **overlap condition** i store the **index values** also, because after selecting a minimum value from any index, change the **value to 0 for that index**.

**Overlap Condition:-** a single element appears in both priority Queues. 

# Complexity
- Time complexity:O(N)
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

- Space complexity:O(N)
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    long long totalCost(vector<int>& costs, int k, int c) {
        int n = costs.size();
        priority_queue<pair<int,int>> pq1,pq2;
        long long ans = 0;
        int i  = 0,j = n-1,count = 0;

        while(count<k)
        {
            while(i<n && pq1.size()<c)
            {
              pq1.push({-1*costs[i],i});  
              i++;
            }
            while(j>=0 && pq2.size()<c)
            {
              pq2.push({-1*costs[j],j});
              j--;  
            }

            while(pq1.size()>0 && costs[pq1.top().second]==0)
            pq1.pop();

            while(pq2.size()>0 && costs[pq2.top().second]==0)
            pq2.pop();


            if(pq1.size()>0 && pq2.size()>0)
            {
               if(abs(pq1.top().first) <= abs(pq2.top().first))
               {
                   ans+=abs(pq1.top().first);
                   costs[pq1.top().second] = 0;
                   pq1.pop();
                   count++;
               }
               else
               {
                   ans+=abs(pq2.top().first);
                   costs[pq2.top().second] = 0;
                   pq2.pop(); 
                   count++;
               }
            }
            else if(pq1.size()>0)
            {
                   ans+=abs(pq1.top().first);
                   costs[pq1.top().second] = 0;
                   pq1.pop(); 
                   count++;
            }
            else if(pq2.size()>0)
            {
                   ans+=abs(pq2.top().first);
                   costs[pq2.top().second] = 0;
                   pq2.pop();  
                   count++;
            }
        }
        return ans;   
    }
};
