# Intuition
To have two windows of size equal to candidate and to get minimum of both windows of overall cost.

# Approach
1. This question can be solved using min heap.
2. We have to hire in k sessions. 
3. Lets consider two indices ```l=0``` and ```r=n-1``` where n=costs.size();
4. Also take two min heaps to create the window.
5. We have to add elements in each k sessions in either or both min heaps.
6. We will add element at index ```l``` in first min heap and ```r```in second one.
7. We will take care about the size of each min heap should be less than candidates.
8. After this, we will get the minimum in both min heap.
9. If the minimum belongs to first one then we will pop from first min heap otherwise same from second one.
10. This minimum value will be used in making of overall cost.

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
 $$O(nlog(n))$$ 

- Space complexity:
$$O(n)$$

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    long long totalCost(vector<int>& costs, int k, int candidates) {
        int n=costs.size();
        int l=0,r=n-1;
        priority_queue<int,vector<int>,greater<int>>pq1,pq2;
        long long cost=0;
        for(int i=0;i<k;i++){
            while(pq1.size()<candidates&&(l<=r)){
                pq1.push(costs[l]);
                l++;
            }
            while(pq2.size()<candidates&&(l<=r)){
                pq2.push(costs[r]);
                r--;
            }
            long long top1=INT_MAX,top2=INT_MAX;
            if(pq1.size()>0){
                top1=pq1.top();
            }
            if(pq2.size()>0){
                top2=pq2.top();
            }
            if(top1<=top2){
                cost+=top1;
                pq1.pop();
            }
            else{
                cost+=top2;
                pq2.pop();
            }
        }
        return cost;
    }
            //<!-- Please upvote if you liked -->
};
